commit.message:
Merge pull request #5 from Badg/master

Unlicense/public domain
Added support for explicit specification of daemonization re-invocation command on windows
General use of starred expansion is not allowed in python 3.4
I don't claim to understand travis cfg files
Partial code cleanup and fix typechecking for windows signal handler
Changed ReceivedSignal to DaemonikerSignal (and added alias for backwards-compatibility). Changed its parent to BaseException, because by default it should be system-exiting.
Added print to stderr (instead of just logging) when an error occurs after daemonization within context manager
Slightly modified assignment order of variables and found the typo resulting in parent not exiting.
The worst thing about inter-process coordination is, well, inter-process coordination
Traceback import was missing and I need it to debug a failure!
When stylistic cleanup accidentally breaks your build, bad lessons are learned
Substantially improved support for error handling in Daemonizer context manager
Fixed several bugs in windows signal handling
Unfortunately, this test code is very fragile
